OL,3,CWhy are energy bills going up and how
OL,4,Ccan you save money?
OL,6,FThe snow is falling - our bills are
OL,7,Fnot.
OL,9,FMid-winter Energy costs are rising
OL,10,Ffrom January for 34 million customers
OL,11,Fon tariffs regulated by the official
OL,12,Fprice cap. But why is this happening
OL,13,Fdespite wholesale prices actually
OL,14,Ffalling?
OL,16,FFriday's energy price cap announcement
OL,17,Fbrings average annual bills to #1,758
OL,18,Fin January, a small rise of just 28p a
OL,19,Fmonth, but wholesale prices have
OL,20,Fdropped 4%. So why are we paying more
OL,21,Ffor energy?
