OL,3,CWhy are energy bills going up and how
OL,4,Ccan you save money?
OL,6,FSome fixed tariffs are 10% below the
OL,7,Fprice cap, and some customers could
OL,8,Fsave almost #200 a year. One leading
OL,9,Fcomparison site (USwitch) tells me 26
OL,10,Ffixes currently beat the price cap.
OL,12,FIt's not always about switching your
OL,13,Ftariff; many people can save just by
OL,14,Fchanging their payment method. You can
OL,15,Fcut bills by #47 on average by direct
OL,16,Fdebit pre-payment.
OL,18,FThen there are all the tips about
OL,19,Freducing energy use, easier said than
OL,20,Fdone in these temperatures.
